
This directory is intended for PlatformIO Test Runner and project tests.

Unit Testing is a software testing method by which individual units of
source code, sets of one or more MCU program modules together with associated
control data, usage procedures, and operating procedures, are tested to
determine whether they are fit for use. Unit testing finds problems early
in the development cycle.

More information about PlatformIO Unit Testing:
- https://docs.platformio.org/en/latest/advanced/unit-testing/index.html

Simulator smoke test:
- Run `./scripts/run_simulator_smoke_test.py` from the repo root.
- The script builds `env:simulator`, creates a temporary `fs_`, copies a test EPUB into it, opens common screens, renders them, drives reader page/menu input, and fails on crashes or missing success output.
- Use `--book path/to/book.epub` to choose a specific EPUB and `--page-turns 10` to change how far the reader flow navigates.
- Use `--theme lyra-carousel` to run the flow with a specific UI theme. Supported names include `classic`, `lyra`, `lyra-extended`, `roundedraff`, and `lyra-carousel`.
- Use `--no-build` to reuse the existing simulator binary or `--window` to show the SDL window instead of running headless.

Expected coverage:
- This is a fast regression tripwire, similar to a small browser smoke test. It proves the simulator can boot, open common screens, load the selected EPUB, turn pages, open reader menus, and exit without crashing or hanging.
- It is useful for catching activity entry/render crashes, bad allocations, uncaught exceptions, assertions, segfaults, AddressSanitizer/UndefinedBehaviorSanitizer reports, obvious hangs, and EPUB/theme-specific failures for the exact book and theme under test.
- It also covers a narrow scripted reader path: page forward, open the reader menu, enter Reader Options, navigate/toggle one option, and back out to the reader.

Limits:
- It does not replace hardware testing. The desktop simulator has different memory, filesystem, timing, display, sleep, button, battery, USB, Wi-Fi, and OTA behavior than the ESP32-C3 device.
- It should not be expected to catch exact hardware heap pressure, SD-card locking/timing issues, e-ink ghosting or refresh quality, real deep-sleep wake behavior, electrical button behavior, subtle visual layout problems, or EPUB cases that are not present in the selected test book.
- After a simulator pass, still verify important changes on hardware with the same EPUB and theme by turning pages, opening the reader menu, entering Reader Options, toggling a setting, backing out, and watching for crashes or memory-related logs.
